    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Combine<strong> half </strong>your<strong> peri peri spice mix</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a bowl with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri marinade</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken thighs</strong> to the bowl and mix well until they're fully coated</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken </strong>and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 17-18 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri chicken</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (\ud83d\udd04 10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>in 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>remaining peri peri spice mix</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, bring to the boil and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is done, transfer to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Add the <strong>pulled chicken</strong>, <strong>cooked pepper</strong> and <strong>drained pasta </strong>to the peri peri sauce with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce begins to stick to the<strong> </strong>pasta \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri chicken & pepper pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-chicken-and-pepper-farfalle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Serve the<strong> peri peri chicken & pepper farfalle </strong>with the<strong> salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
